gamerule.reloadRegistries.description: Worldgen Devtools: Extend the /reload and /datapack enable|disable commands to reload all registries, such as worldgen definitions.
gamerule.syncAfterRegistryReload.descrip: Worldgen Devtools: Syncronize changes to all clients (including in singleplayer) after a registry reload, such as biome colors and trim patterns. Disabling this enables faster reloads.
gamerule.maxChunkStatus.description: Worldgen Devtools: The maximum worldgen status of newly generated chunks.
gamerule.applyProcessorLists.description: Worldgen Devtools: Apply configured processor lists to generated jigsaw structures.
gamerule.keepJigsaws.description: Worldgen Devtools: Keep Jigsaw blocks after jigsaw structure generation.
gamerule.applyGravityProcessor.descripti: Worldgen Devtools: Apply the gravity processor to terrain matching jigsaw structure pieces.
gamerule.saveChunks.description: Worldgen Devtools: Turning this OFF will disable any world saving, so that reloading the world will regenerate it. Already saved chunks are not deleted.
